excerpt: Oceanside 75-ft. waterfall cascading from a cliff, with its waters flowing into the sea.
detail_description: Seogwipo Jeongbang Waterfall is a stunning 75-ft. cascade that plunges directly into the ocean, making it the only waterfall in Korea to do so. While swimming isn't recommended, visitors can wade into the water and get close to the waterfall during low tide. The surrounding area offers picturesque views of Sojeongbang waterfall from an observatory and provides a perfect spot for a picnic lunch on the rocks near the water.
name: Seogwipo Jeongbang Waterfall
address: 37 Chilsimni-ro 214beon-gil, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: A walk in lush natural surrounds with shops & food stands leads to this scenic waterfall & park.
detail_description: Cheonjiyeon Waterfall is a picturesque natural attraction located in a lush park area with shops and food stands. The name "Cheonjiyeonpokpo" means "sky connected with land," reflecting the heavenly appearance of the waterfall as it cascades down. The surrounding wooded area is home to diverse flora, including rare plants like brambles, songyeopnan, gusiljappam trees, sanyuja trees, and camellias.
name: Cheonjiyeon Waterfall
address: Seogwipo, South Korea

excerpt: Indoor market established in the 1960s with stalls selling produce, seafood & household goods.
detail_description: Seogwipo Olle Market is an indoor market that has been around since the 1960s, offering a variety of stalls selling fresh produce, seafood, and household goods. Located in Seogwipo, the second-largest city on Jeju Island in South Korea, this market is part of a region known for its rocky volcanic coastline and stunning natural landscapes.
name: Seogwipo Maeil Olle Market
address: 18 Jungang-ro 62beon-gil, 특별자치도 Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Dramatic cliffside views are the highlight of this scenic lookout point with trails & swimming.
detail_description: Oedolgae, also known as Independence Rock, is a striking sea stack located off the coast of Jeju. Rising 20 meters above the sea, this freestanding rock formation offers dramatic cliffside views and can be easily accessed via a short walking track. Situated in the southern part of the island, it is a popular spot for visitors to enjoy its photogenic beauty throughout the day. To avoid crowds and capture the best light, early morning or late afternoon visits are recommended.
name: Oedolgae
address: 791 서홍동, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Modern, cable-stayed pedestrian overpass with a sail-shaped tower, illuminated at night.
detail_description: Saeseom Island Saeyeongyo Bridge is a modern, cable-stayed pedestrian overpass with a sail-shaped tower that lights up beautifully at night. It connects to Saeseom Island and offers stunning views of Seogwipo port area. The island itself is known for its natural beauty and is a great spot for birdwatching.
name: Saeseom Island Saeyeongyo Bridge
address: 40 Namseongjung-ro, Seogwi-dong, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Casual dorms & private rooms in a cool hostel featuring a cafe, a courtyard & complimentary Wi-Fi.
detail_description: Mido Hostel is a trendy accommodation located in the vibrant city of Seogwipo, just a short walk from Olle Traditional Market and Lee Jung Seop Art Street. The hostel offers both single-sex dorms and private rooms, all featuring bunk beds with amenities such as private curtains, reading lights, and sockets. Renovated in 2015, the hostel boasts a peaceful atmosphere popular among Koreans.
name: Mido Hostel
address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo-si, 서귀동, 258-2

excerpt: Scenic estuary lined with cliffs of volcanic rock, popular for kayaking & traditional-raft rides.
detail_description: Soesokkak, a famous tourist attraction in Jeju, is a scenic estuary known for its volcanic rock cliffs and popular activities like kayaking and traditional-raft rides. The area's name comes from the shape of a lying down cow, formed by the meeting of freshwater from Hyodoncheon Stream and saltwater. This hidden gem along Seogwipo spans seventy miles and offers breathtaking views reminiscent of landscapes in Oman and Japan.
name: Soesokkak
address: 138 Soesokkak-ro, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Lively street named for a well-known artist who lived here, with art galleries, studios & cafes.
detail_description: Lee Jung Seop Street is a vibrant and culturally significant area in Seogwipo, known for its art galleries, studios, and cafes. It holds geographical importance as it was where the renowned Korean artist Lee Jung-Seop created some of his greatest paintings. The street hosts various events, festivals, and street concerts, making it a burgeoning center of culture and art.
name: Lee Jung Seop Street
address: Seogwi-dong, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Museum featuring the works of late painter Lee Jung Seob in his restored former home.
detail_description: The Lee Jung Seob Art Gallery is a must-visit museum in Jeju, South Korea. It opened its doors in 1995 and offers a unique experience for art enthusiasts. The gallery showcases the masterpieces of Lee Jung-Seop, as well as paintings by renowned artists Park Soo-Keun and Lee Ung-No. Visitors can explore the restored former home of the late painter, gaining insight into his life on Jeju Island.
name: Lee Jung Seob Art Gallery
address: 27-3 Ijungseop-ro, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: The Seogwipo Submarine offers a unique and unforgettable experience for tourists visiting Jeju. Descending to depths of 40m, this submarine allows you to marvel at the vibrant marine life surrounding the island. The activity is family-friendly, providing an adventure that is both enjoyable and safe. With English translations available during the commentary, visitors can fully appreciate the sights as they journey underwater.
name: Seogwipo Submarine 西歸浦谮水艇
address: 40 Namseongjung-ro, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: Wind 1947 offers an exhilarating cart riding experience on its 1,947m track, one of the longest in the country. The scenic views of Mount Halla add to the thrill. Unlike other vendors, Wind 1947 provides go-karts for two people, allowing you to enjoy the ride with a partner or child. The price is reasonable and there's a waiting area with a cafe and souvenir shop.
name: Wind 1947
address: 78-27 Topyeonggongdan-ro, 특별자치도, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: Saeseom, also known as Sod Island, is a charming and tiny island located at the mouth of Seogwipo Harbour. Accessible via the picturesque cable-stayed Saeyeon-gyo bridge, this island offers a delightful boardwalk trail that takes less than an hour to complete. The well-maintained trail provides stunning views of the surrounding area, including Munseom Island. Despite its nickname as Bird Island, it may not always be teeming with avian life.
name: 새섬
address: Seogwi-dong, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: Jeju Olle Trail Course 6 is a 13.3km route that offers a perfect balance of length and difficulty, making it one of the top attractions on Jeju Island. The trail takes about 4 hours to complete, offering diverse terrains with beaches, waterfalls, volcanoes, and monuments along the way. From Soesokkak to Jeju Olle Traveler Center, hikers can enjoy coastal views and stunning natural scenery while walking through mountain paths or trails.
name: Jeju Olle Trail Course 6
address: Chilsimni-ro, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Exhibits about green tea, an observatory with countryside views & a popular gift shop & cafe.
detail_description: Nestled in Jeju, Osulloc Tea Museum offers a delightful experience for tea enthusiasts. The museum showcases the cultural significance of tea in Korea and other regions, featuring various types of tea and green tea-infused dishes. Visitors can explore exhibits on green tea, take in panoramic countryside views from an observatory, and browse through a popular gift shop and cafe. While the museum itself is relatively small, it provides easy access to nearby attractions like Innisfree and delectable dining options.
name: Osulloc Tea Museum
address: 15 Sinhwayeoksa-ro, Andeok-myeon, 특별자치도, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: National park with a large mountain, featuring many alpine plants, hiking trails & sweeping views.
detail_description: Hallasan National Park, located on Jeju Island in South Korea, is centered around the majestic Hallasan Mountain, the highest peak in the country. The mountain is surrounded by 368 parasitic volcanoes known as Oreums and offers sweeping views of the island. Designated as a national park in 1970, it is a haven for alpine plants and provides numerous hiking trails for outdoor enthusiasts to explore its geological wonders.
name: Hallasan National Park
address: 2070-61 1100로, 특별자치도, Jeju-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Family-friendly locale for viewing teddy bears in costumes & lifelike poses, plus cafe & gift shop.
detail_description: The Teddy Bear Museum, located in Jeju, offers a delightful experience for visitors of all ages. The museum showcases a diverse collection of teddy bears dressed in various costumes and lifelike poses, including designer teddy bears that are more than just toys. You can also admire antique teddy bears and even the world's smallest teddy bear. This family-friendly attraction is an ideal alternative to Loveland and is perfect for travelers with kids.
name: Teddy Bear Museum
address: 31 Jungmungwangwang-ro 110beon-gil, 특별자치도, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Rugged cliff face formed from angular volcanic pillars of rock & listed as a national monument.
name: Jusangjeollidae
address: Jungmun-dong, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Quiet, seafront beach area offering a lighthouse, restaurants & shops, plus scenic views & trails.
detail_description: Seopjikoji is a serene coastal area on the eastern shore of Jeju Island, offering a picturesque lighthouse, charming restaurants, and shops. The iconic Seopjikoji Lighthouse sits atop a hill with breathtaking ocean views and is locally believed to have wish-granting powers. This elegant white building has been featured in popular dramas and holds romantic significance for some.
name: Seopjikoji
address: Seopjikoji-ro, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Modern aquarium with many species, plus reptiles, penguins, a food court & gift shop.
detail_description: Aqua Planet Jeju is a modern aquarium located on Seopjikoji, boasting the title of the largest in Asia. It offers an immersive experience into the world of ocean ecology, featuring over 48,000 animals and plants. Visitors can explore diverse marine life including stingrays, sharks, seals, penguins, and otters. The aquarium also hosts captivating shows such as the Haenyeo Diver display and an underwater musical performance called "Looking for Sena.
name: Aqua Planet Jeju
address: 95 Seopjikoji-ro, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Museum devoted to optical-illusion art, with quirky, 3D paintings, sculptures & objects.
detail_description: Alive Museum Jeju is a quirky museum devoted to optical-illusion art, featuring 3D paintings, sculptures, and objects designed for fun photo opportunities. The museum offers helpful guides in English to assist visitors in capturing the perfect nonsensical snap. With various interactive art pieces and illusions, it's an interesting place for families, couples, and friends to visit. Additionally, there are go-karts available for added entertainment.
name: Alive Museum Jeju
address: 42 Jungmungwangwang-ro, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: A popular place to walk, this rocky coastline features unique cliff formations & scenic ocean views.
detail_description: Yongmeori Coast is a must-visit destination for nature enthusiasts. This rocky coastline offers stunning cliff formations and picturesque ocean views. The area is easily accessible by car, with the drive from Suweolbong to Sanbangsan and Yongmeori Coast taking around 30 minutes. Along the way, travelers can enjoy breathtaking coastal vistas and make stops for photo opportunities.
name: Yongmeori Coast
address: 112-3 Sagye-ri, Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Restored 1890s village featuring more than 100 structures & displays of period artifacts.
detail_description: Jeju Folk Village is a restored 1890s village that showcases over 100 structures and period artifacts. It's famous for being the filming site of the hit TV series Dae Jang Geum. The attraction features 117 houses depicting scenes from different village lives, including Mountain Village, Hill-Country Village, Fishing Village, and Shamanism Village. Visitors can explore traditional wedding halls and even enjoy horseback riding picture-taking zones.
name: Jeju Folk Village
address: 631-34 Minsokhaean-ro, Pyoseon-myeon, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Large, scenic botanical garden featuring a massive, contemporary greenhouse with many plant species.
detail_description: Yeomiji Botanical Garden is a vast and picturesque botanical garden that boasts a modern greenhouse housing numerous plant species. The indoor garden spans 3 acres and features a towering observation tower at its center, along with diverse floral and plant exhibitions such as the Mystery Garden, aquatic gardens, cactus gardens, jungle gardens, and tropical fruits garden. Additionally, the outdoor gardens cover 24 acres and showcase various themed areas including Japanese, Korean, French lawns, and more.
name: Yeomiji Botanical Garden
address: 93 Jungmungwangwang-ro, 특별자치도, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Compact beach & surfing spot with large waves, showers & access to a nearby eatery.
detail_description: Jungmun Saekdal Beach is a popular spot located in the flamboyant Jeju Resort Complex on the south coast of Jeju Island. It offers large waves, making it a great surfing destination, and amenities such as showers and access to nearby eateries. The beach is conveniently situated just a short drive from Jeju City International Airport, making it easily accessible for visitors. Families will find plenty of attractions in the area, including iconic landmarks suitable for children of all ages.
name: Jungmun Saekdal Beach
address: Saekdal-dong, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Adult-only sex-education displays at a sleek, modern museum with erotic sculptures in the gardens.
detail_description: The Museum of Sex and Health is a modern, adult-only museum in South Korea that offers sex education displays and erotic sculptures in its gardens. Located on Jeju Island, the museum features funny and sex-related exhibits, making it a popular destination for honeymooners. Despite South Korea's conservative attitude towards sex on the mainland, Jeju Island embraces a more open-minded approach. The museum promotes inclusive language and a sex-positive environment with interactive components and multilingual signs.
name: Museum of Sex and Health
address: 1611 Iljuseo-ro, Andeok-myeon, 특별자치도, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Opened in 1979, this year-round arboretum on 20 hectares offers many camellia & other plant species.
detail_description: Camellia Hill Botanical Garden, situated on a 20-hectare expanse inland from the south coast of Jeju Island, is a year-round arboretum that boasts an impressive collection of over 6,000 camellia trees representing more than 500 species. The garden also features diverse plant displays, including a large glass house showcasing various flora.
name: Camellia Hill Botanical Garden
address: 166 Byeongak-ro, Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

name: 송악산
address: South Korea, Seogwipo-si

excerpt: Rocky peak with a scenic hike, seasonal photo ops with yellow rapeseed blooms & a Buddhist temple.
detail_description: Sanbangsan, also known as Sunset Peak, is a rocky peak on Jeju Island with scenic hiking trails and seasonal photo opportunities with yellow rapeseed blooms. It features different trails, including one leading to the Sanbanggulsa cave temple about 150m above sea level. The area is surrounded by gardens and has a Buddhist temple at the foot of the hill.
name: Sanbangsan
address: Seogwipo-si, South Korea

excerpt: Glass-art theme park with indoor & outdoor displays, a children's forest & hands-on activities.
detail_description: Jeju Glass Castle is a unique glass art theme park in Jeju, featuring both indoor and outdoor displays, a children's forest, and hands-on activities. The park boasts the world's first all-glass labyrinth, as well as the world's largest glass ball and glass diamond among 250 delicate glass models exhibited in six themed model parks. Visitors can explore the exhibition hall to marvel at these intricate glass creations that give the place an ethereal vibe.
name: Jeju Glass Castle
address: 462 Nokchabunjae-ro, Hangyeong-myeon, Jeju-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Hilltop Buddhist temple offering ornate designs & colorful statues, plus vast water & cliff views.
detail_description: Bomunsa Temple, located on a hilltop, is a stunning Buddhist temple with intricate designs and colorful statues. The temple offers breathtaking views of the southern sea of Jeju, making it a picturesque spot for visitors. While the temple itself may not be grand, the outdoor exhibits and the panoramic backdrop make for an unforgettable experience. Visitors can explore the temple grounds for free and enjoy unreal views of the sea while making wishes and prayers.
name: Sanbangsan Bomunsa Temple
address: 218-10 Sanbang-ro, Andeok-myeon, 특별자치도, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: KIMYOUNGGAP GALLERY DUMOAK is a tribute to the late photographer Kim Young Gap, who captured the serene beauty of Jeju for 15 years before his passing from Lou Gehrig's disease. The gallery showcases his emotive photography, offering a unique perspective on the island's changing seasons and hidden landscapes that touch the hearts of visitors. The artist's inspiring story adds depth to his moody and emotion-evoking works.
name: KIMYOUNGGAP GALLERY DUMOAK
address: 137 Samdal-ro, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Museum showcasing vintage cars with a kids’ ride, souvenir shop & outdoor walking path.
detail_description: The World Automobile & Piano Museum in Jeju, South Korea is a must-visit destination for car enthusiasts and history buffs. The museum offers a fascinating journey through the evolution of the automotive industry, showcasing an impressive collection of classic cars from renowned global brands. Visitors can also enjoy driving small electric cars around the museum and explore an animal petting zoo with their children.
name: World Automobile & Piano Museum
address: 1610 Jungsanganseo-ro, Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Amusement park with coasters, a carousel & a 4D theater, plus street snack trucks & a food court.
detail_description: Shinhwa Theme Park is part of Jeju Shinhwa World, offering a variety of attractions for visitors to enjoy. The park features thrilling rides, themed zones, and entertainment suitable for families with kids. In addition to the exciting coasters and 4D theater, there are also food options available at the street snack trucks and food court. Visitors can also make use of the indoor and outdoor pools with massage jets at Shinhwa Water Park within the same complex.
name: Shinhwa Theme Park
address: 98 Sinhwayeoksa-ro 304beon-gil, Andeok-myeon, 특별자치도, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: Hwanguji Natural Pools in Jeju Island offer an adventurous and refreshing swim experience in a stunning ocean-fed rock pool. The landscape features a lone dog rock on the horizon, a lovely walking track, and even a fairy tub. Although it may be closed at times due to waves or falling rocks, visitors can still enjoy the beautiful coastal walk with shaded paths and wooden walkways. While swimming is currently restricted, the area remains a picturesque spot for nature lovers to explore and admire.
name: Hwanguji Natural Pools
address: 서홍동, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Museum dedicated to the history of technology of air & space travel, with a cafeteria & shops.
detail_description: The Jeju Aerospace Museum, the largest of its kind in Asia, is a captivating destination for aviation enthusiasts and families alike. It offers a comprehensive look into the history of air and space travel, with indoor and outdoor exhibits showcasing 26 aircraft. The museum also features interactive displays, hands-on activities for kids, and a flight simulator suitable for all ages.
name: Jeju Aerospace Museum
address: 218 Nokchabunjae-ro, Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Protected high-altitude wetlands & wildlife area featuring rock formations, trails & scenic views.
name: 1100 Highland Ecological Swamp
address: Saekdal-dong, 특별자치도, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Leafy garden filled with miniature replicas of global landmarks including cathedrals & palaces.
detail_description: Soingook Theme Park, located in Jeju, South Korea, is a major tourist attraction spread over 20,000 square meters of land. The park features miniature replicas of famous landmarks from around the world, including Bulguksa Temple and Tower Bridge. Visitors can also enjoy traditional cultural experiences and hands-on programs. The park offers an outdoor concert stage, mini RC car stadium, and dinosaur fossils. Additionally, there are English information panels available for visitors to learn about the structures.
name: Soingook Theme Park
address: 347 Hwasunseodong-ro, Andeok-myeon, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: Chocolate Land is a delightful destination nestled within the Jungmun Tourism Complex in Jeju-do, perfect for chocolate enthusiasts and curious travelers alike. While it may not be the most thrilling attraction on its own, it offers an engaging experience with unique features like chocolate paintings and even kimchi-flavored chocolate! Visitors can immerse themselves in the World Chocolate Exhibition Hall, where they can learn about chocolates from around the globe and participate in fun chocolate-making classes.
name: Chocolate Land
address: 2864-36 Saekdal-dong, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: The World Seashell Museum on Jeju Island is a unique and artful museum that showcases a diverse collection of seashells from around the world. The museum offers an unforgettable experience with its well-organized displays and creative presentation of shells, appealing to both marine biology enthusiasts and those who appreciate beautiful exhibits. Visitors are pleasantly surprised by the thoughtful curation, which presents shells in quirky and artistic ways, making it a great way to spend time on the island.
name: World Seashell Museum
address: Seogwipo, South Korea

excerpt: Scenic, serene park with many flowers & plants, plus pony rides & small animals, such as pigs.
detail_description: Hueree Nature Life Park, located on Jeju Island, is a serene and scenic destination perfect for a family outing. The park features an array of flowers, plants, and sculptures, with the main attraction being the Canola Flower Field. Visitors can also enjoy pony rides and interact with small animals such as pigs, horses, chickens, and rabbits. Additionally, there's an opportunity to pick halabong oranges and feed the famous black Jeju pigs.
name: Hueree Nature Life Park
address: 256 Sillyedong-ro, Namwon-eup, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: Pyoseon Beach, located on the southeast coast of Jeju Island, offers a variety of activities for visitors. Horseback riding programs include training courses, outdoor rides through cedar forests and along the beach from October to April. The beach itself is known for its stunning sunrise views and unique round lake shape that shines with various colors during low tide. It's a spacious area where visitors can relax, sunbathe, or swim without feeling crowded.
name: Pyoseon Beach
address: Pyoseon-ri, Pyoseon-myeon, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Korean handicrafts & artworks displayed in a contemporary building designed by Tadao Ando.
detail_description: Bonte Museum, which means "original form" in Korean, is a contemporary museum located in southwest Jeju. It was established in 2012 to showcase both traditional Korean art and contemporary artworks from around the globe. The museum complex comprises several buildings housing five galleries and other facilities, all seamlessly connected by gardens designed by renowned Japanese architect Ando Tadao. Visitors can explore various exhibits including traditional Korean crafts like wooden tray-tables and wrapping cloths, as well as modern art installations.
name: Bonte Museum
address: 69 Sallongnam-ro 762beon-gil, Andeok-myeon, 특별자치도, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

name: 마린스테이지_퍼시픽리솜(Marine Stage_Pacific Resom)
address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo-si, 특별자치도, Jungmungwangwang-ro, 154-17, KR

detail_description: Eongtto Falls, located in the countryside of Jeju, is a hidden gem that becomes truly magnificent after heavy rainfall. The area features a cafe operating on an honor system and offers stunning views of the roaring waterfall during stormy days. Although it may not be as accessible as other waterfalls in Jeju, it's definitely worth a visit and doesn't cost anything to enter. The falls are usually dry, so visitors should be prepared for that possibility.
name: Eongtto Falls
address: 121-4 Yeomdon-ro, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: The Chocolate Museum, located in the south of Jeju Island, is the second largest of its kind globally. Built with volcanic scoria, it seamlessly blends into the island's natural landscape. Visitors can explore the history of cacao, learn about chocolate production, and indulge in sweet tastings. The museum's unique exterior resembles an ancient fortress and houses various exhibitions showcasing delectable chocolate treats. Additionally, visitors have the opportunity to participate in chocolate-making classes for a hands-on experience.
name: Chocolate Museum
address: 551-18 Ilgwa-ri, Daejeong-eup, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: Jeju Horse Park is a spacious and impressive area to see horses, with modern windmills providing a cool backdrop. Visitors can enjoy various packages for horse rides, including walks in the forest and mini runs. The friendly staff make it an enjoyable experience for all ages, as even a 60-year-old had her first horse ride there. It's recommended for families, offering affordable prices and operating even on weekends.
name: Jeju Horse Park
address: 381-15 Noksan-ro, Pyoseon-myeon, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

excerpt: Park offering many themed gardens, sculptures & walks in Micheon Cave, a large lava tunnel.
detail_description: Ilchul Land is a large park in Jeju Province that offers various themed gardens, sculptures, and walks within the expansive Micheon Cave lava tunnel. It is a popular attraction in the area, featuring a Footbath cafe where visitors can enjoy an aroma foot spa to soothe tired feet. The park is suitable for leisurely strolls and also appeals to fans of the "Running Man" show.
name: Ilchul Land
address: 4150-30 Jungsangandong-ro, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: Bunker des Lumières, situated in Seongsan, Jeju, is an immersive media art exhibition housed in a bunker. It offers a captivating experience through the use of images, sound, and light. Currently showcasing the works of Monet, Renoir Chagall and Paul Klee, this exhibition creates a unique harmony with classical & jazz music alongside the beautiful paintings of these masters.
name: Bunker des Lumières
address: 89-17 Seoseongil-ro 1168beon-gil, 특별자치도, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: GENIUS LOCI: YUMIN ART NOUVEAU COLLECTION is a stunning art gallery located within the Glass House, designed by Tadao Ando as part of the Phoenix Island resort complex. The Glass House itself is a remarkable structure made of glass and concrete, offering panoramic views over the sea to Seongsan Ilchulbong (Sunrise Peak).
name: GENIUS LOCI: YUMIN ART NOUVEAU COLLECTION
address: Goseong-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea

detail_description: The Citrus Museum offers an educational and enjoyable experience for families. Visitors can explore the museum to learn about citrus fruits and their cultivation. While citrus picking may not be available year-round, there are other activities such as a playground for kids and even a cookie making class. It's important to check the seasonal availability of citrus picking before planning a visit. Additionally, visitors should verify the museum's operating hours as they may differ from what is displayed on informational boards.
name: Citrus Museum
address: Seogwipo, South Korea
